{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"lupine-clearcut-mare","description":"## What\n\nGenerate the MCP tool reference from the server's own tool registry, so LLM clients\nhave an always-accurate tool list and the hand-maintained catalog in `CLAUDE.md`\ncannot drift. Second of the two high-value interface inventories.\n\nTemplate the `scripts/gen_env_registry.py` generator + CI drift-gate pattern.\n\n- Add `scripts/gen_mcp_reference.py` (new): enumerate tools from the MCP server's\n  `list_tools()` registry (`src/rebar/_mcp` or equivalent), emitting `docs/mcp-reference.md`\n  with a generated header. It MUST distinguish the read-only vs write (live) profiles\n  and note which tools are gated by `REBAR_MCP_READONLY` / `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM` /\n  `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_JIRA_SYNC`.\n- Wire a CI drift gate mirroring the env-registry gate.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `docs/mcp-reference.md` is generated from the live tool registry and marked\n      generated.\n- [ ] The reference correctly separates read-only from write/live-gated tools.\n- [ ] A CI drift gate fails when the committed reference is stale.\n- [ ] Adding/removing an MCP tool changes the generated output (verified).\n\nFiles: `scripts/gen_mcp_reference.py` (new), `docs/mcp-reference.md` (new/generated),\n`.github/workflows/test.yml`.","id":"235a-e6c1-e034-4a75","parent_id":"4191-b4f9-146a-43cd","priority":2,"tags":["docs","generated","p1"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"P1: Generate the MCP tool reference (generator + drift gate)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783814583191992001,"uuid":"b41d991a-efe1-4aa2-b9c1-a6eadc5c7ea9"}